OL,3,CHigh Court challenge against Met over
OL,4,CFreemason declaration policy thrown out
OL,6,FHe said: "The purpose of such action,
OL,7,Fand therefore the purpose of the
OL,8,Frequirement to disclose the
OL,9,Finformation, is the dual one of
OL,10,Feliminating the potential for actual
OL,11,Fbias, where officers discharge their
OL,12,Ffunctions improperly, and perceived
OL,13,Fbias, where there is a perception or
OL,14,Fsuspicion that officers are
OL,15,Fdischarging their functions improperly.
OL,17,F"In both cases, the requirement is, in
OL,18,Fmy judgment, 'designed to secure the
OL,19,Fproper exercise of the functions of a
OL,20,Fconstable'. The contrary is not
OL,21,Freasonably arguable."
