OL,3,CHigh Court challenge against Met over
OL,4,CFreemason declaration policy thrown out
OL,6,FIn written submissions, the barrister
OL,7,Fsaid that the move was an
OL,8,F"institutional signal of suspicion"
OL,9,Fwhich breached Freemasons' human
OL,10,Frights and was based on "limited,
OL,11,Fopaque and heavily perception-driven"
OL,12,Fevidence.
OL,14,FShe continued that the police appeared
OL,15,Fto rely on "long-standing conspiracy
OL,16,Ftheories and/or prejudicial tropes
OL,17,Fabout Freemasons" as a reason to
OL,18,Fintroduce the measure.
