OL,3,CHigh Court challenge against Met over
OL,4,CFreemason declaration policy thrown out
OL,6,FBarristers for the Met said the claim
OL,7,Fshould be thrown out, telling the
OL,8,Fcourt that the suggestion officers
OL,9,Fwould be blacklisted was "plainly
OL,10,Fwrong and that employees were "free to
OL,11,Fbecome or remain Freemasons".
OL,13,FJames Berry KC, for the force, said in
OL,14,Fwritten submissions that claims that
OL,15,Fthe decision breached officers' and
OL,16,Fstaff's human rights were "without
OL,17,Fmerit", and that fears of
OL,18,Fstigmatisation are "not supported by
OL,19,Fthe evidence".
