OL,6,FDiscussing the "stigma associated with
OL,7,FFreemasonry", he said: "The defendant
OL,8,Fis not responsible for the stigma; but
OL,9,Fthe defendant is responsible for
OL,10,Faddressing it, in connection with the
OL,11,Fexercise of police duties and
OL,12,Ffunctions by the defendant's officers
OL,13,Fand staff, and for positively
OL,14,Fmaintaining public confidence in the
OL,15,Fimpartiality and transparency of the
OL,16,FMetropolitan Police."
